headline: How Investors May Respond To Kinder Morgan (KMI) 2025–2026 Earnings Guidance And Planned Dividend Increase
summary: Kinder Morgan recently issued 2025–2026 guidance, projecting net income attributable to the company of US$2.90 billion in 2025 and US$3.10 billion in 2026, alongside an expected annualized 2026 dividend of US$1.19 that would extend its dividend growth streak to nine consecutive years. This combination of higher anticipated earnings and continued dividend growth highlights Kinder Morgan’s focus on cash generation and returning capital to shareholders through a mature, fee-based infrastructure...
